place_description: Stylish cafe for gourmet coffee, sandwiches & pastries in a chic space with lots of seating options.

reviews_data.review_text: Very calm and relaxing atmosphere.

Got here at 6:30am, not too crazy for a business district. No baked goods. No skim, 1%, 2%. The 8oz macchiato is about 3 ounces. "That's how we do it here", snarky look from barista. So if you want to spend  $4.50 for a shot of espresso with foam because that's how it's done, this is your place.
Atmosphere is amazing but the coffee isn't great.

Walked in and loved the scenery right away. I was looking forward to this because of all of the picture I had seen. I went up to the counter to order and my mood turned upside down. The service from the lady with glasses behind the counter was horrible. Her mood was so bad and had even forgotten the cronut my sister had ordered and we had to go back and ask again and she wasn't even apologetic and made it like it was my mistake. I saw her do that for another family too. Dropped my overall experience from a 10 to a 2. Everyone else was so nice and helpful.

Very nice spot. Good parking is hard to find, though. I have tried a few different drinks there and haven't been disappointed with any of them. Plus the atmosphere is unlike most coffee places I've been to. 100% worth checking out

Every time I visit Charlotte I have to stop here. My favorite coffee shop i've been to with the most unique and wonderful atmosphere. The employees are always so kind and my coffee is always perfect. I always have to add a sugar or milk to my lattes at other coffee shops but i never have to alter what i'm served here. Love it!
Coffee taste really bad!! The place is cute tho. Interesting concept.

This is a cute coffee shop inside the Charlotte Marriott City Center! They had a variety of snacks, sandwiches, pastries and drinks. The seating here is made for all types of people! See pictures for what I mean! My latte coffee was smooth and better than Starbucks! My donut cronut was so good, I ate the entire thing!

Staff was sweet and helped me make a pastry decision!

The cashier girl couldn't even smile or say hello. Then I told her I was staying here and my (burnt milky) cappuccino came out in a paper cup. I also ordered an egg and cheese, which they put the wrong name on so I sat there for 15 minutes with no sandwich then when I asked she was like oh you can have this one thats been sitting here for 15 minutes. It was cold so I asked for a fresh one.

When something like this happens, a business and it's employees should go above and beyond to rectify the situation. Especially somewhere that charges high prices for sub par food and drinks.

Overall, I would not come back and don't recommend it.

P.s. I've never written a bad review before so I'm not some trolling person, I just think this business needs to do better.

I was excited to try out this cold brew on my walk home. The service was spot on and the space is absolutely gorgeous. I have to get them credit on these points for sure. That being said... I love cold brew coffee. I especially love trying cold brew from newer and local coffee shops. This cold brew thankfully IS cold brew and not iced coffee, which is always my fear. But for $6 + tip, this coffee is clearly cheaply made to pursue the most profits. I wish I could say it wasn't but at that inflated of a cost, I'd expect a much better taste rather than the darker, slightly burnt quality. Tastes more like concentrate than a true cold brew.
Cool coffee shop to kill some time with friends.
The shop is a little pricey in my opinion, but that is to be expected given the location. Very cool layout inside, good for relaxing or working for a few hours.
Quirky atmosphere, loved it. Great coffee, quick service

Love the atmosphere the most. Great for writing, people watching and to enjoy a coffee. Their cronut with key lime is yummy, a bit too much sugar tho, and hard to eat without getting the sugar all over.
Nice coffee and salads

Kofe khorosh
Inter'er khorosh
Devushka s fingalom za barom smeshnaia
Great espresso, very chill atmosphere, and the sausage breakfast sandwich is better than McDonald's.
My coffee was done as soon as I was done ordering - it was delicious and exactly as I ordered!
So fun and funky! Great place for working or relaxing. My latte was perfectly creamy and they had a variety of food items.

I don't know how this place gets good ratings...we went and staff were downright rude, tables all dirty, and food was pretty mediocre and not fresh or high quality. We definitely would give it at most two stars overall.
Chill space to work.

Ordered small soy latte with no foam, emphasized twice no foam. The barista did not smile at all looked to be pissed that she had to work. Gave me the coffee and surprise, there was foam. I asked her to please remake it and she did very angrily I might add and it had foam again. I informed her that she only had to use a spoon to strain the foam off when pouring the steamed soy milk but she was not interested. I combined the two coffees myself removing the foam which resulted in less than half a cup remaining from the two coffees to be discarded. Perhaps she was having a bad day but unfortunately in the service industry the customers should not see your attitude. Siri and will definitely be avoiding this coffee shop moving forward.
Comfortable, unpretentious environment and coffee. Enjoyed a breakfast sandwich as well. Will return when in the area.
My friend and I met there. It was quaint and great vibes. She enjoyed herself and I as well. They are like Starbucks. It's just more organic. I recommend it.

The French toast muffin was amazing. The yogurt parfait was good. The cappuccino had an odd flavor to it, so I'll try something else next time.
Nice space and convenient location.

Fantastic, coffee shop. Espressos are fantastic. We liked the service in the coffee shop. They do a nice job and have some very interesting spaces to sit and relax.  Definitely come check this one out when you're in town, it's worth a visit!!
Coffee was decent. Extremely overpriced but fast. But don't worry service was terrible.
I only got their latte but they offer food as well. The baristas are really nice and patient and when we went they had a dog adoption so we got to meet puppies!!!! Definitely recommend
We tried a few different drinks and the butterfly matcha and Rocky Road latte were favorites. The service was great. The cashier was friendly and the barista was fast and efficient. Great atmosphere

This is such a cute coffee shop.

While home for a week I found myself patronizing the same coffee shop. As such, my sister suggested I try another one.

We stopped in after having lunch downtown. I will say that this spot is more ideal for patrons that are already downtown. If you are not, you will have to find parking on the street( which will likely have a  cost!).

When we walked in there were ample staff at the counter. I ordered an unsweetened  matcha latte with oat milk. I love the fact that they offer both a  pre- sweetened and a non sweetened option! My drink was made quickly.

We opted to dine in to enjoy the unique seating options. They have  a sitting area that is directly on the stairs. They have pillows  out for a little extra cushion. It's such a  vibe!

In addition to the cute vibe, they have a small retail  section.  They  had a number of flavored syrups for sale and popcorn.

If you are in the area I would strongly suggest stopping on.
Spacious, cozy, unique.

Visiting Charlotte for the first time, I selected Coco & the Director for my morning cappuccino and croissant.  I found the service to be acceptable, but really no personal touch.  This was a bit surprising given the establishment wasn't overly busy.

I ordered my cappuccino dry.  While the flavor was full bodied, the presentation and blend wasn't worth a second attempt.

Hats off to Marriott for branding Coco, but I would consider this a coffee house nor a Co-Lab as it is branded.

Should you find yourself in the fourth ward, Charlotte uptown, you may want to explore a little more, and find an alternate place to enjoy a cup.
Very nice coffee shop. Friendly employees and coffee is great!
Something's can be very costly but atmosphere is very nice...
Came by at 530 and they were closed. Supposed to be open until 6

Fun coffee shop downtown!

I loved the atmosphere if this place and there's TONS of seating areas and options- I highly recommend going here if you have some work to do or reading- very cool and very conducive to work in my opinion.
There's tables and different sections you can go to if you need a little bit of privacy.

I got my usual latte, which was just ok. Got their cinnamon cronut, which was not as sweet as expected- it was cinnamon and buttery and flaky like a croissant, but I expected it to be more sweet- so just adjust expectations if you're getting that.

All in all I recommend giving this place a shot if you're downtown!

Love this place  Their coffee menu is so simple but delicious, and their food selection is always so fun and healthy. This place is also so cute and staff is always sweet. I really love the atmosphere of this place, it's very calming
It's a nice place and decent coffee. But they served it in a take away cup. I was expecting a proper coffee cup and the famous Cronuts  were sold out too early.
Amazing atmosphere, and even better tea. Worth the wait in line  I wish I could give this place 100 reviews, by far my favorite coffee shop ever.
I like this cafe here good coffee and cozy atmosphere
Good place to have short bites and hot coffees
Bad service and bad attitude, filled my cup not even half way and when I kindly asked she gave me sass and said only this once and a little bit.

Wish there was an equivalent to this in South End. Great coffee and a good divergence from the classic southern industrial vibes of Charlotte. Will be coming back. Great for studying, meeting with someone, killing time etc
They make an amazing cappuccino very fluffy and strong
Can't make a cappuccino
Coffee as well as latte were absolutely delicious!
The coffee tastes phenomenal and the space itself is quite a nice cozy space to sit down relax and have a conversation with friends.

Great atmosphere, the macchiato was delicious, and the croissant too! If you need coffee and a snack, you know where to go.

The espresso roast isn't bitter the way most American places are these days, and that may be because of the Italian feel.
The people, the place is perfectly laid out and I love showing up and enjoying my beverage and or sandwich...thanks for what you do Coco and how you do it!!
i actually got a friendly human on the phone at 6am (no voicemail greeting stating options) when they first opened to discuss parking so i can get in & out. dirty chai are awesome.
The coffee is a bit thin, though no signs of astringency. Really cool space with nice people behind the bar. Probably a bit overpriced, but really good spot to hang out.
Nice smooth latte for a Wednesday morning. Cool place to start the day off. Wish I had more time to chill
Lovely coffee place right in the downtown of Charlotte!
Cute and quiet little coffee shop
I study here all the time.  I give them 4 stars because the close super early for a coffee shop lol
Positive upbeat atmosphere, good amount of seating, very relaxing, great smoothies, good sandwiches
This place looks small on the outside but it is huge inside! Coffee was great, croissant was great, and tons of seating areas. Would come here 10 times out of 10 instead of Starbucks!
S'mores latte was the bomb!!
Good coffee, good service, ample seating, snacks & outlets!

Amazing interior design in this coffee house; one of the best I have seen anywhere.  Unfortunately no warm breakfast options were available as they did not have a cook for the day.  Their sandwich warmer was broken.  Otherwise 5/5 coffee spot.
Great coffee house. I love their iced chai.
Nice cozy dining area inside, park at The Green and walk towards the cafe. Nice ambiance.
Neat coffee shop.

Such a fun coffee shop! Lots of unique places to get seated for work or a conversation over coffee. The platform steps and cushions are so fun! Coffee was declined and despite busy line moved very quick!

This spot is a GEM. I was in the city staying at the Marriot for a few days and decided to give this cute coffee shop a try - I am so glad I did! The coffee was great and Sally was delightful at the register. She made my whole day. I can't wait to come back to try the pastries!
Rude costumer service, I asked a lady if they had parking. She answered with a horrible attitude.
Food and coffee is great but batista is too slow in preparing drinks. Need 25 mins of time to pickup a coffee

coffee = strong and tasty ... that's expected.  The pastries are always fresh in the morning.  But, it's the service that really takes it to the next level.   I work downtown tues/thurs and genuinely look forward to stopping in and seeing all of the staff; who are cheerful, pleasant and full of energy even at 7am.  Sally, who is usually on the register, is a rockstar.  I always take my clients to stop by for coffee when they are in Charlotte to experience it too - perfect for casual meetings.
Wife got a Flat White and we both tried the Cronuts.  All was Fantastic
Come here and relax for breakfast and/or lunch! The cinnamon cronut is delicious as is the bacon, egg, and gouda sandwich.
Such a cute place to study or hang out! My go-to!

I'd come back for the atmosphere alone. Great place to spend the day getting work done! Coffee wasn't the best but I didn't try anything else. The pastries/food looked delicious. Can't wait to go back!
Food was OK, pricey; tables were w not clean, shelves were dusty, front door glass dirty.
Delicious cronuts!
Excelente cafe

For anyone that cares about their coffee the latte was just not good. way too much foam with air bubbles. Espresso was bitter and since it was not busy so definitely expected more. On top of that if I'm Paying $5.17 for a small I want it to be good. Would suggest the 5 min walk to not just coffee inside 7th street market.
Great coffee spot. Plenty of space to hang out
Long waits for drinks and very overpriced

We had an exceptional experience at this coffee shop, and what made it stand out was the fact that it wasn't part of a chain. The beautiful decor, good coffee, and friendly staff added to the charm. While the cronut didn't quite live up to the hype, all the other pastries were fantastic. Interestingly, the coffee shop is located in the Marriott lobby, making it a unique find. The place was very clean, and the restroom facilities are within the Marriott, ensuring convenience.
This is by far the best coffee shop in Charlotte.

Place with a very cool vibe and micro-climate I should say where you you can relax on the steps, work studiously on the tables and also have team conferences.

Coffee is great too!
They sell soda.  Also the service is very friendly
The monotone "okay" girl has got to go. Said "okay" 5 times then my total. Not a single thing more.

Pretty much just stopped here on a whim.  We closed out the Discovery Place Science. We didn't have much to do until much later in the evening and were in the mood for a snack.  We saw this spot as we walked and we just gave it a try.  Good thing we did.  We really enjoyed our drinks and pastries.  The  coffee and scone were  , they were my favorite.  The ambiance was cool, pretty laid back despite being dead smack inside inside a business/financial building.  Prices were up to par with everything else in the area.  The staff was friendly.  Definitely a must try.
Good place for a rush coffee. Cronuts look better than they are.

My cousin said the coffee wasn't good.
The architecture and design are really cool but the seating options are uncomfortable.
I liked that most people were there to work but the place was way too loud. Most of the their lighting comes from the windows so it's too dark on raining days.

This place at least to me is pretty new. What a neat little coffee shop with plenty of places to sit and enjoy their wellcrafted drinks. Right in the middle of the city I really like this place it will be back for sure. On this day I had a chai te latte but others enjoyed their other coffee drinks. Recommend.
Very cozy atmosphere with a great tasting ice mocha coffee.
This is such an aesthetic and cool place to visit! The staff was very nice and there were so many places to sit and study.

Coco and the Director is my favorite coffee shop in Charlotte! The staff is super friendly and helpful, and the coffee is amazing. They have a wide selection of drinks and food, from lattes and smoothies to sandwiches and pastries. The pastries are delivered fresh from a local French bakery every morning, and they are delicious. I especially love the banana bread and the croissants. The coffee shop has a cozy and modern vibe, with plenty of seating options. They have a loft-style second level, a stadium seating area, and a co-lab space for local makers and community collaboration. The location is also great, right in the heart of Uptown, inside the Marriott Hotel. I highly recommend Coco and the Director to anyone who loves coffee and good vibes. 5 stars!
Coffee shop that has a trendy atmosphere. The cold brew was delicious and also the breakfast sandwich. My only complaint was small size tea was a little pricey at $4.
Such a cute atmosphere! I ordered a Banana Nut Bread Latte. It was DELISH!

Cronut tasted pretty good, the coffee was a bit too sweet.
Service wasn't really friendly. I ordered a latte with almond milk but when I saw the server make it with normal milk, I reminded her that I ordered almond milk and she just made the same coffee with normal milk again?!?
It is also pretty overpriced.

Nice coffee spot in a uptown Charlotte. Attached to the Marriott, you can access this shop from trade street or from inside the hotel.

Coffee is good -- and the baristas take their time in making well-balanced drinks. Some of the flavored lattes are overly sweet -- such as the cinnamon / brown sugar options, so you may want to ask for light flavor.

There is nice seating options -- some are "upstairs", or you can sit in the hotel or business office atrium. Easy spot for a meeting uptown -- if you're walking; cannot imagine parking is convenient or affordable (if you parked with the hotel).
This is a 5 star coffee shop, this is also a work environment, this is also very relaxing.  Oh the espresso is really interesting, has a nice nutty flavor.  This is a must go.
Really cool place, great cronuts and coffee
One of the few consistent coffee shops I go to. Top 5 for studying in Charlotte for me.
Delicious pastries, good coffee, interesting interior. An iced coffee and scone will run you nearly $15. Definitely a barrier to entry!
Amazing coffee drinks and a great atmosphere! We will be back!!
Workers are Great,, Service was awesome,,,good delicious
Great location and a wonderful service.
Wonderful coffee shop. Drip coffee was nice and easy to drink. Prices are reasonable. There is lots of seating, including levels with pillows to sit on. Just an overall nice vibe and experience.
Love working here. The ambience and vibes is great for creatives.
Beautiful cafe with friendly staff. I ordered an iced chai latte with oatmilk, latte, cronut and a chicken panini. Everything tastes great. Highly recommended!
Consistently good coffee with a great atmosphere. Perfect spot to hang out for a bit
Really nice atmosphere to meet with a group and share ideas.
Cute coffee shop. The latte and smoothie I had were not worth the prices - not using the best ingredients. Had a cronut though and those are always delicious!

Saw this location on Tik tok and decided to try it. This coffee shop has cronuts, prosecco AND sandwiches.  OMG.  A little pricey for a coffee shop. Instantly fell in love with the vibe of the space.  Cozy and welcoming to folks that need a change of scenery working remote and a nice place to have a casual lunch business meeting.  Great location.
I loved it here. Dropped in for a quick breakfast with my family, it was a bit of wait for the coffee but there was a line.
The ambience is great!! Such a cute place! Although coffee wasn't great.

This place used to be good.  Let's not confuse the well-designed space with good food and service experience. Despite adequate staffing, service is especially slow for no reason. I've  witnessed people walk out of line when they were next.  The food is marginal and they replaced the divine Sugarman cronuts with their own knock off version that is essentially, tasteless sugar dough. They likely capitalize on the flow between the hotel and corporate building, but they will be in for the fight of their lives once this large food court area opens in the same building/block. Overpriced and under-delivering.

Amazing! Excellent place for co-working or meeting with colleagues. The coffee was fantastic! Loved all the large tables they had to encourage either community seating or meeting with colleagues. Will definitely head back here on my next trip.

This is a super cool coffee shop downtown! The interior is modern and cozy, lots of wood and black metal, ambient lighting, and different seating areas. I didn't get any food, but saw they had a sandwich station, in addition to serving pastries and some packaged/pre-made salads and sandwiches.

I had the cinnamon bun latte and liked it! Was on the sweeter side, but that's what I enjoy for coffee. This is a great atmosphere for working or studying; I need to come by again with my laptop!
One only barista working w/ a long line of people. Latte wasn't too good
Loved the ambiance and great coffee.
Cute atmosphere
Always a jumping spot.  Sometimes it might be a little bit hard finding a seat.
Really nice coffee shop with great atmosphere. Really nice to come and be able to do some work or just enjoy the city. They make really good lattes here, also.
Very rude
Coffee is okay but their cronuts are a must! But be there early because they sell out super fast!

Horrible experience. Cashier is incredibly unpleasant and did not even look at us the whole transaction (pink hair). Pastry had hair and she just gladly took it back without apologizing or asking if they could offer something else. Horrible customer service. You do not have to be obnoxiously nice but just be a decent being. People come first thing in the morning and that's what they get to experience. Awful. Manager/assistant manager was nice though.
Doesn't take cash no sign. Service is trash
Had an awesome smoothie that was filling and satisfying.
Great coffee and great vibes!!! Sit on the stairs. The textures in the place are great. I just wanna chill here.
Coffee and environment is always good

Really nice place!!
Very cozy. The coffee was good, the cronut was good, even though it was coated with too much sugar, the banana bread was delicious.
It was a great way to start our morning.
This joint has the best pastries in uptown, along with great coffee!
The best latte in my life!!!
Great coffee, amazing location, cozy vibe

Decided to try a different coffee spot than my usual go-to on the weekends. It's cozy and unique, but the coffee was BAD and the service so-so. My husband got a regular drip coffee which tasted like nothing. I ordered an Americano with sugar free vanilla. I watched the barista pour wayyy too much syrup in the cup (I was a barista for 5 years so I have a good idea about how much goes in a 16oz cup) and then watched 2 or 3 more drinks that were ordered after me get made and handed out before mine. They were relatively busy, with a line of 3 people pretty consistently, so I don't mind waiting for my coffee in those situations. However, the drink was so gross it didn't redeem the wait. I had my husband try it to make sure I wasn't being overly critical and he suggested I throw it away. We left and tossed our drinks and went to another coffee shop. Won't be visiting this spot again.
Lots of seating. Drinks and food were delicious. Perfect experience for a rainy day in the city.
Best place to study and work. Coffee is good!
No option to tip workers while using a card, coffee tastes like water
Good coffee and pastry.
Breakfast sandwiches are definitely delicious and the place is comfortable and inviting.
I love it is the one of the best coffees i tried

The cronuts are amazing.  The cream filled is outstanding and not too sweet.  Good coffee.  My only complaint is that the breakfast sandwiches take a while to come out and I think maybe they forgot.  It was not busy on a Monday at 8:15am.
Really cute little shop. Slow but worth the wait if you have the time. I got hot chocolate and it was nice and creamy and a little on the dark side rather than sweet.

This coffee shop is the absolute cutest. Latte with sugar free hazelnut was perfect! Sausage, egg and cheese English muffin was sooo good!! Fresh made to order eggs. I love the different seating areas in here, and sections. There's an area with pillow seats, and another side with lounge chairs and tables. Really enjoyed our coffee and breakfast. Baristas we're also so friendly and nice!! Will be back.
Everything was nice except coffee was not very hot for 6:30 in the morning.
Great atmosphere and vibe. Coffee and variations are fantastic.
Friendly atmosphere and an easy place to read, study, or hangout.
I work across the street and find myself getting coffee here when I have time and the baristas and cashiers are always so nice! A very welcoming space to chill as well.
It's really cool place with a nice atmosphere, a good place to work with a laptop. But their coffee isn't so good
Try the hunnybun latte. Soooo tasty!!

Awful. just plain awful. Terrible customer service, and subpar coffee. I can't believe the unprofessionalism at the front counter (you're met with utter disdain and condescension). Everyone behind is so snarky and nasty. The joy now is telling all my friends to avoid this place!
Coffee was so so. And there were no coco. Weird store name with no coco.

This used to be my favorite coffee shop in Uptown until my two most recent incidents. Just completely awful, reckless customer service. First incident was with a blond girl wearing a hoodie with a rainbow at the front counter; second incident was with a black man at the front counter.

Problem A: Both times when I asked for my drink of choice ("Could I have a ____") they responded with something to the rude tune of "Yeah no." The second encounter I was thrown off by how dismissive he was; both times they just kept staring at me like I was the one who was foolish. How am I supposed to know what's out of stock? That's your job to inform me, do so respectfully, and perhaps offer a suggestion. So instead had to re-pivot and offer a second choice, without any input from them. Again just poor customer service based on their reactions.

Problem B: In that second incident, after I ordered, I moved to the right to wait for my order; a customer came over afterward and told me she had heard the blond girl and black man (at the front counter) talking smack about me. They were condescending to what I was wearing and how I wasn't entertaining their flippant manner with my demeanor.

Seriously have these two ever gone through customer service training? How can the Marriott endorsement this terrible behavior? The baristas here used to be so sweet (one used to remember my name) and now they're moody, condescending, and just awful to deal with. Will happily take my money to Night Swim or the cafe in the Ritz. Bye bye.
Delicious coffees with strong flavor and comfortable rustic decor with unique seating areas for cool ambiance.
the place was not crowded and they took 15 minutes or more to do my smoothie. nice place but all durty
Service is slow and my breakfast sandwich looks like someone sat on it.     That being said, the sandwich and coffee was good.
Great place to sit and enjoy a snack. The banana bread is very good.
Great spot to get coffee uptown. Really a fun overall space too.  Great place to meet or study

I love this place.  Came Sunday at noon on September 11.
Yummy food and coffee.  Amazing service... I wish I would've gotten their names but shout out to my "hot sauce in my bag" ladies with fabulous pastel pink hair and amazing blue winged eyeliner!!
Dope interior space with a great ambiance. Iced coffee was strong, which is an automatic five from me.

A totally unique setting, very original and cozy with lots of space.  The menu is pretty big, however the food/drinks take is just OK and nothing to rave about.  The staff was pretty friendly except for the cashier who looked brand new and did not know what she was doing.  Still good enough to grab something on the go

Visiting from out of town. Drove into the city just to try this place.. It has taken almost an hour since we arrived to wait in line, place order, and now still waiting on food/drinks. At 10am on a Sunday. Just writing this to let others know to expect a wait.. not a quick service type of place. Otherwise the pasties were bomb and I am hopeful for the coffee but haven't received it yet :)

Great location and atmosphere. Pricey but expected with location being in the city.  If you are staying at the Marriott, there is access from within.  Would have given 5 stars if service was more efficient (long lines) and ability to customize breakfast sandwiches (basically warm pre-made and give to you).  Cronuts were the highlight!

Would give 4 stars based on wait time and ease of the experience but the pastries and coffee were definitely 5/5 and the staff were nice.

We ordered two pour overs, the blueberry muffin, and the donut cronut. Doesn't seem like only a take-out place but they didn't ask if it was for here or to-go and I couldn't eat the cronut donut out of the large box so we had to ask for a plate.
We were told the pour overs would take 5 minutes, not a big deal at all but it took 18 minutes .

Worth the wait but room for improvement.
Bacon egg croissant was good. The dirty Chai tea awful.
Great coffee place - the cafe has lots of fun seating and the drip coffee was really nice - it was a Tanzanian blend. Try the cinnamon sugar cronut - what a treat!

Very cool place but their coffee wasn't the best!
It is for sure a very nice atmosphere and environment... however, they could do better with the quality of easy products. Their cold brew was very average
Absolutely love coming here! Great place to work when you don't want to work from home, delicious treats and drinks to accompany a busy and focused work day

The coolest coffee shop in Charlotte. I feel like I'm in NYC when I'm sitting inside, they have such a unique setup for seating. I always get an iced mocha, and it's a perfectly balanced blend of espresso, chocolate, and sugar.

This place is everything you want a coffee shop to be. Long hang outs... pillows, tables, chairs, alternative seating, artisanal baked goods, grab and go snacks, Wi-Fi, and a thousand charging stations.

The feng shui is generally good - there is ample, varied space to create your own experience. That is the highlight of this cafe. On the drinks end, the espresso I had was so acidic I thought i was drinking battery juice. Meanwhile, my partners chai favored the sweeter side of life, but not all things can be so sweet.

Coco and the Director is literally one of my favorite spots to get coffee in Uptown. You wouldn't even be able to tell that attached to the hotel because that's how amazing it is.

The inside of the shop is absolutely beautiful. Super boho vibey and the perfect spot to lounge with your laptop. I love all of the cool seating that they have. I visit Coco & the Director at least once a week or once every other week and get the same thing everytime, but I know for a fact the other options are great also. My order is an Iced Latte with vanilla bean & mocha syrup with light ice - absolutely delicious!!!

Charged $75 for a cup of coffee. Went to the location and spoke with a manager. She agreed it was an error, would resolve, and would follow up with me. Left my contact info but never heard anything. Called over a week later and left messages asking her to call me back for an update. Coffee is fine but $75/cup is too steep.
Stopped by for espressos, good coffee and fast service. No parking around there

Definitely not as good as I expected.  Breakfast sandwiches are microwaved and limited to two options (which is fine for a coffee shop) and not at all customizable, just wanted to swap English muffin for croissant but absolutely not, since they are pre made and microwaved.  Didn't get to try baked goods as cronut wasn't put on our order and didn't catch that until after it was rung up and our food came out because the cashier didn't repeat anything.  Definitely not going back.

The decor was really charming and they had a pretty expansive drink menu. This is however one of the most average coffee shops I've ever been to. The service was just okay and I'm attributing that to the employees being overwhelmed, therefore no harm no foul there. Their breakfast options were a bit basic, though not bad. If you're close by and need coffee and a quick breakfast you're in luck.
Good
Very clean and orderly.
Reasonably priced, excellent service, kind of cute service 2, and quite Frankly,  The best bacon egg and cheese croissant I've ever had

When I go to a Cafe the one thing that bothers me the most is the one size option. If I wanted a small cup of coffee I would order a small. I asked for a larger latte and when I saw the cup I said I ordered a large latte
She said this is the only size we offer. And I ordered a pastry. It was hard as a rock. We were there for a work meeting. And we ordered a few items for our staff. We all had purchased something to eat. I then asked for a plate she looked under wherever they should be and she said were all out.. They were all dirty. So they handed me a stack of to go boxes. Honestly I was really disappointed. I would say maybe next time. But I won't be coming back. Take care of your place. Customer service is a crucial part of today's broken world.
